{"timestamp": "2026-05-28 16:14:22,902", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_7\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\n\\nYour task is to take interview. The following are the steps\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Parse the job description to extract required skills, experience levels, and core competencies\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_title\\\": null,\\n  \\\"seniority_level\\\": null,\\n  \\\"department\\\": null,\\n  \\\"employment_type\\\": null,\\n  \\\"location / remote_policy\\\": null,\\n  \\\"required_skills\\\": [],\\n  \\\"preferred_skills\\\": [],\\n  \\\"required_experience_years\\\": null,\\n  \\\"educational_requirements\\\": null,\\n  \\\"key_responsibilities\\\": [],\\n  \\\"compensation_range\\\": null,\\n  \\\"flags\\\": [\\n    \\\"Job description text missing. Please provide the job description to extract required skills, experience levels, and core competencies.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Conduct the technical interview session using the generated questions and record candidate responses\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Send scheduling and follow-up emails to the candidate using job and candidate data\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on the extracted job requirements\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nJSON\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with software development methodologies (e.g., Agile, Scrum, Waterfall). Which do you prefer and why?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Software Development Methodologies\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Demonstrates understanding of various methodologies, explains preference with justification, and provides examples of successful implementation.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"Can you describe a situation where you had to adapt a methodology to fit a specific project?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you handle conflicting priorities within an Agile sprint?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between a stack and a queue data structure. Provide a use case for each.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Data Structures\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Clearly defines stack (LIFO) and queue (FIFO), provides relevant use cases (e.g., stack for function calls, queue for task scheduling).\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"What are the time complexities of common operations on stacks and queues?\\\",\\n        \\\"How would you implement a queue using two stacks?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"What are the key principles of object-oriented programming (OOP)? Give examples of each.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Identifies encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism, and abstraction, and provides concrete examples of each principle.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How does inheritance promote code reuse?\\\",\\n        \\\"Explain the difference between abstract classes and interfaces.\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe a time you had to debug a complex software issue. What steps did you take to identify and resolve the problem?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Problem Solving & Debugging\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Presents a structured approach to debugging (e.g., reproducing the bug, isolating the cause, testing fixes), highlights tools used, and emphasizes learning from the experience.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"What debugging tools are you most familiar with?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you approach debugging code written by someone else?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of version control and its importance in software development. Which version control systems have you used?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Version Control\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Understands the purpose of version control (e.g., tracking changes, collaboration), mentions Git (or other systems), and describes common operations (e.g., commit, branch, merge).\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"Explain the difference between 'git merge' and 'git rebase'.\\\",\\n        \\\"Describe a situation where you had to resolve a merge conflict.\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Design a simple REST API for managing a list of books (including endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting books).\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"API Design\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes RESTful principles, defines appropriate HTTP methods and endpoints, specifies request and response formats (e.g., JSON), and considers error handling.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How would you handle authentication and authorization for this API?\\\",\\n        \\\"How would you implement pagination for large lists of books?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of database indexing. How does it improve query performance, and what are the trade-offs?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Database Concepts\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Understands how indexes work (e.g., creating a lookup table), explains the performance benefits for read operations, and acknowledges the overhead for write operations.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"What are the different types of indexes?\\\",\\n        \\\"When would you choose not to use an index?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with testing frameworks and methodologies. What types of tests have you written (e.g., unit, integration, end-to-end)?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Software Testing\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Demonstrates familiarity with testing frameworks (e.g., JUnit, pytest, Selenium), explains the purpose of different test types, and provides examples of writing effective tests.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you measure code coverage?\\\",\\n        \\\"Describe a situation where you had to write a test for legacy code.\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of caching. What are the different types of caching, and when would you use each?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Caching Strategies\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Understands the purpose of caching (e.g., reducing latency, improving performance), describes different caching layers (e.g., browser, CDN, server-side), and provides use cases for each.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you handle cache invalidation?\\\",\\n        \\\"What are the trade-offs between different caching strategies?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with cloud computing platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP). What services have you used, and what are their benefits?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Cloud Computing\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Demonstrates familiarity with cloud platforms, mentions specific services (e.g., EC2, S3, Azure Functions, Google Cloud Storage), and explains the advantages of cloud computing (e.g., scalability, cost savings).\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you approach infrastructure as code in the cloud?\\\",\\n        \\\"What are the security considerations when deploying applications to the cloud?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T16:14:22.902149\"\n}"}
