{"timestamp": "2026-05-28 16:14:39,467", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T16:14:39.467330\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on the extracted job requirements\", \"result\": \"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with software development methodologies (e.g., Agile, Scrum, Waterfall). Which do you prefer and why?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Software Development Methodologies\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Demonstrates understanding of various methodologies, explains preference with justification, and provides examples of successful implementation.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\":...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n- The questions provided are very general and not specifically tailored to the extracted job requirements.\\n- We need to reference the actual job’s key technologies, frameworks, and competencies (e.g., Python, Django/Flask, REST API design, AWS services, Docker/Kubernetes, CI/CD pipelines, performance tuning, testing frameworks).\\n- The output should reflect those specifics in each question, ideal answer, and follow-up probes.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your recent experience building RESTful APIs in Django (or Flask). Which features of the framework did you leverage and why?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Web Frameworks / REST API\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"References Django REST Framework (serializers, viewsets, routers) or Flask Blueprints; explains authentication/authorization choices; mentions request validation and error handling.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you structure your URL endpoints and serializers?\\\",\\n        \\\"What strategy did you use for pagination and filtering?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the Global Interpreter Lock (GIL) in CPython. How does it affect concurrency, and what approaches have you used to work around it?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Python Concurrency\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Understands GIL; distinguishes threading vs multiprocessing; mentions async/await, multiprocessing module, or external task queues (e.g., Celery).\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"Can you give an example where you switched from threads to async code?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you decide between multiprocessing and an external task queue?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe how you set up containerized deployments using Docker. What considerations did you make for configuration, layering, and security?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Containerization / Docker\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions Dockerfile best practices (small base images, multi-stage builds); environment variables; secret management; reducing image size; scanning for vulnerabilities.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you handle environment-specific configuration?\\\",\\n        \\\"What steps do you take to secure your Docker images?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with AWS (e.g., EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda). Which services did you use for scalability and cost-optimization?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Cloud Architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes use of auto-scaling groups, load balancers, serverless functions; cost monitoring with AWS Cost Explorer; data storage choices (S3 vs EFS vs RDS).\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you design your VPC and subnets for security?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics did you monitor and how did you respond to alerts?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"What testing frameworks and methodologies have you applied in your Python projects? Describe your approach to unit, integration, and end-to-end tests.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Testing / Quality Assurance\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions pytest or unittest; fixtures and parameterization; mock/patch; CI integration; test coverage reporting; testing in CI/CD pipeline.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you test asynchronous code or external service calls?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you measure and enforce code coverage?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Given a microservice handling user requests, how would you design and implement caching to reduce database load? Which layer(s) would you cache?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Performance & Caching\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Discusses Redis or Memcached; selects in-memory vs distributed cache; cache key design; TTL, invalidation; cache-aside vs write-through strategies.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you handle stale data or cache stampede?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics would you track to measure cache effectiveness?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Design a CI/CD pipeline for a Python web service deployed on Kubernetes. Include steps from code push to production rollout.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"CI/CD / DevOps\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"References Git branching strategy; build/test in Jenkins/GitHub Actions/GitLab CI; Docker image build and push; Helm charts or Kubernetes manifests; blue/green or canary deployments.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you roll back a failed deployment?\\\",\\n        \\\"What automated checks would you include before merging to main?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"A customer reports your service is slow under peak load. Walk me through your profiling and optimization process in Python.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Debugging & Optimization\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions cProfile, line_profiler, or py-spy; identifies hotspots; algorithmic improvements; database query optimization; concurrency vs batching; caching.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you verify the fix under load?\\\",\\n        \\\"What trade-offs did you consider between complexity and performance gain?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain how you would secure API endpoints handling sensitive user data. What layers of security would you implement?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Security Best Practices\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes HTTPS/TLS; OAuth2/JWT; role-based access control; input validation; rate limiting; logging/auditing; secrets management.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you rotate and store secrets?\\\",\\n        \\\"What steps do you take to detect and respond to security incidents?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}"}
