 with AWS services such as EC2, S3, RDS, and Lambda. How did you design for scalability and cost-optimization?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Cloud Architecture / AWS\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes Auto Scaling Groups, ELB/ALB, S3 lifecycle policies, RDS read replicas, serverless functions; cost tracking via Cost Explorer or Trusted Advisor.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you architect your VPC/subnets for security?\\\",\\n        \\\"Which CloudWatch metrics and alerts did you configure?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"What testing frameworks and methodologies have you used in your Python codebase? Describe your approach to unit, integration, and end-to-end tests.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Testing / Quality Assurance\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions pytest or unittest; usage of fixtures, parametrization, mocks/patch; integration tests with Docker containers; Selenium or Playwright for E2E; CI integration.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you test async code or external API calls?\\\",\\n        \\\"What thresholds or tools do you use to enforce code coverage?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Given a microservice with a Python API and PostgreSQL backend, how would you design and implement caching with Redis to reduce database load?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Performance & Caching\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Discusses Redis vs Memcached; cache-aside vs write-through; TTL and invalidation strategies; key naming conventions; fallback on cache miss.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How would you handle cache stampedes or stale data?\\\",\\n        \\\"Which metrics (hit rate, eviction) would you monitor and why?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Design a CI/CD pipeline for a Python/Django service deployed on Kubernetes. Outline steps from code push to production rollout.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"CI/CD / DevOps\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"References Git branching strategy; GitHub Actions, GitLab CI or Jenkins; Docker image build & push; Helm chart deployment; blue/green or canary releases; rollback strategy.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How would you automate security scanning and linting?\\\",\\n        \\\"What health checks or smoke tests run before and after deployment?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"A production endpoint is slow under load. Walk me through your Python profiling and optimization process.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Debugging & Optimization\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions cProfile, py-spy, line_profiler; identifies hotspots; improves algorithms or DB indexes; adds batching or async calls; validates under load test.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you verify performance improvements at scale?\\\",\\n        \\\"What trade-offs did you consider (complexity vs speed)?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"How would you secure REST API endpoints handling PII in a Django or Flask service? What layers of security would you implement?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Security Best Practices\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes HTTPS/TLS; OAuth2/JWT; role-based access control; input validation; rate limiting; logging/auditing; Vault or AWS Secrets Manager for secrets.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you rotate and store API keys or tokens?\\\",\\n        \\\"What processes do you have in place for detecting and responding to security incidents?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-28 16:15:13,566", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_6\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\n\\nYour task is to take interview. The following are the steps\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Parse the candidate’s resume to extract work history, skills, and education details\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"error\\\": \\\"Candidate resume content is missing. Please provide the full resume text so that work_history, skills, and education details can be extracted.\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on the extracted job requirements\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience building RESTful APIs. What frameworks did you leverage and why?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Web Frameworks / REST API\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions frameworks (e.g., Django REST Framework, Flask); explains authentication/authorization choices; mentions request validation and error handling.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you structure your URL endpoints?\\\",\\n        \\\"What strategy did you use for pagination and filtering?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of concurrency. What approaches have you used to work around it?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Concurrency\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Understands threading vs multiprocessing; mentions async/await, multiprocessing module, or external task queues.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"Can you give an example where you switched from threads to async code?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you decide between multiprocessing and an external task queue?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Describe how you set up containerized deployments using Docker. What considerations did you make for configuration and security?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Containerization / Docker\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions Dockerfile best practices; environment variables; secret management; reducing image size; scanning for vulnerabilities.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you handle environment-specific configuration?\\\",\\n        \\\"What steps do you take to secure your Docker images?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with cloud services (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP). Which services did you use for scalability and cost-optimization?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Cloud Architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes use of auto-scaling groups, load balancers, serverless functions; cost monitoring; data storage choices.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you design your VPC and subnets for security?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics did you monitor and how did you respond to alerts?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Screening\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"What testing frameworks and methodologies have you applied in your projects? Describe your approach to unit, integration, and end-to-end tests.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Testing / Quality Assurance\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions testing frameworks; fixtures and parameterization; mock/patch; CI integration; test coverage reporting; testing in CI/CD pipeline.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you test asynchronous code or external service calls?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you measure and enforce code coverage?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Given a microservice handling user requests, how would you design and implement caching to reduce database load? Which layer(s) would you cache?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Performance & Caching\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Discusses caching technologies; selects in-memory vs distributed cache; cache key design; TTL, invalidation; cache-aside vs write-through strategies.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you handle stale data or cache stampede?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics would you track to measure cache effectiveness?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Design a CI/CD pipeline for a web service deployed on Kubernetes. Include steps from code push to production rollout.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"CI/CD / DevOps\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"References Git branching strategy; build/test in CI; Docker image build and push; Helm charts or Kubernetes manifests; blue/green or canary deployments.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you roll back a failed deployment?\\\",\\n        \\\"What automated checks would you include before merging to main?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"A customer reports your service is slow under peak load. Walk me through your profiling and optimization process.\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Debugging & Optimization\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Mentions profiling tools; identifies hotspots; algorithmic improvements; database query optimization; concurrency vs batching; caching.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you verify the fix under load?\\\",\\n        \\\"What trade-offs did you consider between complexity and performance gain?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"Round\\\": \\\"Technical Deep Dive\\\",\\n      \\\"Question\\\": \\\"Explain how you would secure API endpoints handling sensitive user data. What layers of security would you implement?\\\",\\n      \\\"Competency Tested\\\": \\\"Security Best Practices\\\",\\n      \\\"Ideal Answer Indicators\\\": \\\"Describes HTTPS/TLS; OAuth2/JWT; role-based access control; input validation; rate limiting; logging/auditing; secrets management.\\\",\\n      \\\"Follow-up Probes\\\": [\\n        \\\"How do you rotate and store secrets?\\\",\\n        \\\"What steps do you take to detect and respond to security incidents?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Conduct the technical interview session using the generated questions and record candidate responses\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nSend scheduling and follow-up emails to the candidate using job and candidate data\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```text\\n1. Analyze the job description.\\n2. Analyze the candidate resume.\\n3. Candidate resume content missing. Unable to complete resume analysis.\\n4. Generate tailored technical interview questions based on the job requirements.\\n5. Send scheduling email to the candidate:\\n\\nSubject: Interview Invitation - [Job Title] at [Company Name]\\n\\nEmail Body:\\n\\nDear [Candidate Name],\\n\\nWe are pleased to invite you to interview for the [Job Title] position at [Company Name].\\n\\nThe interview is scheduled for [Date] at [Time] [Timezone]. Please confirm your availability.\\n\\n[Optional: Include a brief introduction of the interviewers and the interview format.]\\n\\nYou can use this link to join the meeting: [Meeting Link]\\n\\nIf this time does not work for you, please let me know your availability for other slots.\\n\\nWe look forward to speaking with you.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\nTone Tag: Semi-Formal\\nPersonalization Tokens Used: [Candidate Name], [Job Title], [Company Name], [Date], [Time], [Timezone], [Meeting Link]\\n\\n6. Conduct technical interview using the generated questions.\\n7. Record candidate responses for each question.\\n\\n8. Send follow-up email to the candidate after the interview:\\n\\nSubject: Following Up - [Job Title] Interview at [Company Name]\\n\\nEmail Body:\\n\\nDear [Candidate Name],\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the [Job Title] position at [Company Name] on [Date]. We appreciate you sharing your experience and insights.\\n\\nThe team will be discussing your interview and we will be in touch within [Number] business days regarding the next steps.\\n\\nIn the meantime, if you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out.\\n\\nThank you again for your interest in [Company Name].\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\nTone Tag: Semi-Formal\\nPersonalization Tokens Used: [Candidate Name], [Job Title], [Company Name], [Date], [Number]\\n\\n9. Score candidate responses based on ideal answer indicators and follow-up probes provided for each question.\\n10. Generate final evaluation report including overall score, strengths, weaknesses, and recommendation (hire/no hire).\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T16:15:13.566208\"\n}"}
